{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "RTK Command Rewrite",
  "description": "Rewrites shell commands to use RTK (Rust Token Killer) for 60-90% token savings. Intercepts 100+ commands across git, test runners, linters, build tools, file ops, containers, and infrastructure before execution.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "preToolUse",
    "toolTypes": [
      "shell"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "IMPORTANT: Before executing this shell command, rewrite it with RTK for 60-90% token savings. RTK is installed at C:\\Users\\niles\\.local\\bin\\rtk.exe.\n\n## REWRITE RULES (prefix with 'rtk'):\n\n### Git (70-92% savings)\n- `git status` → `rtk git status`\n- `git log` → `rtk git log`\n- `git diff` → `rtk git diff`\n- `git show` → `rtk git show`\n- `git add` → `rtk git add`\n- `git commit` → `rtk git commit`\n- `git push` → `rtk git push`\n- `git pull` → `rtk git pull`\n- `git branch` → `rtk git branch`\n- `git stash` → `rtk git stash`\n- `git checkout` → `rtk git checkout`\n- `git merge` → `rtk git merge`\n- `git rebase` → `rtk git rebase`\n- `git remote` → `rtk git remote`\n- `git tag` → `rtk git tag`\n- `git clone` → `rtk git clone`\n\n### GitHub CLI (75-85% savings)\n- `gh pr list` → `rtk gh pr list`\n- `gh pr view` → `rtk gh pr view`\n- `gh issue list` → `rtk gh issue list`\n- `gh run list` → `rtk gh run list`\n\n### File Operations (60-80% savings)\n- `ls` / `dir` / `Get-ChildItem` → `rtk ls`\n- `cat` / `type` / `Get-Content` / `head` / `tail` → `rtk read`\n- `grep` / `rg` / `Select-String` → `rtk grep`\n- `find` / `fd` → `rtk find`\n- `diff` → `rtk diff`\n- `tree` → `rtk ls`\n- `wc` → `rtk read` (for line counts)\n\n### Test Runners (90-99% savings)\n- `vitest` / `vitest run` → `rtk vitest`\n- `jest` → `rtk jest`\n- `pytest` → `rtk pytest`\n- `cargo test` → `rtk cargo test`\n- `go test` → `rtk go test`\n- `dotnet test` → `rtk dotnet test`\n- `playwright test` → `rtk playwright test`\n- `rspec` → `rtk rspec`\n- `rake test` / `rails test` → `rtk rake test`\n- `npm test` → `rtk test npm test`\n- `bun test` → `rtk test bun test`\n- `pnpm test` → `rtk test pnpm test`\n- `yarn test` → `rtk test yarn test`\n- `phpunit` → `rtk test phpunit`\n- `mix test` → `rtk test mix test`\n\n### Build Tools (70-90% savings)\n- `cargo build` → `rtk cargo build`\n- `cargo clippy` → `rtk cargo clippy`\n- `cargo fmt` → `rtk cargo fmt`\n- `npm run build` → `rtk next build` (if Next.js)\n- `make` / `cmake` → `rtk make`\n- `dotnet build` → `rtk dotnet build`\n- `go build` → `rtk go build`\n- `gradlew build` → `rtk gradlew build`\n\n### Linters & Formatters (80-85% savings)\n- `eslint` → `rtk lint`\n- `biome` → `rtk lint biome`\n- `tsc` / `tsc --noEmit` → `rtk tsc`\n- `prettier --check` → `rtk prettier --check`\n- `ruff check` → `rtk ruff check`\n- `golangci-lint run` → `rtk golangci-lint run`\n- `rubocop` → `rtk rubocop`\n- `mypy` → `rtk mypy`\n- `pylint` → `rtk pylint`\n- `shellcheck` → `rtk shellcheck`\n- `hadolint` → `rtk hadolint`\n\n### Package Managers (75-80% savings)\n- `pip list` → `rtk pip list`\n- `pip outdated` → `rtk pip outdated`\n- `pnpm list` → `rtk pnpm list`\n- `bundle install` → `rtk bundle install`\n- `cargo install` → `rtk cargo install`\n\n### Containers & Infrastructure (75-85% savings)\n- `docker ps` → `rtk docker ps`\n- `docker images` → `rtk docker images`\n- `docker logs` → `rtk docker logs`\n- `docker compose ps` → `rtk docker compose ps`\n- `kubectl get pods` → `rtk kubectl pods`\n- `kubectl logs` → `rtk kubectl logs`\n- `kubectl get services` → `rtk kubectl services`\n- `terraform plan` → `rtk terraform plan`\n- `terraform apply` → `rtk terraform apply`\n- `helm list` → `rtk helm list`\n\n### AWS CLI (75-85% savings)\n- `aws sts get-caller-identity` → `rtk aws sts get-caller-identity`\n- `aws ec2 describe-instances` → `rtk aws ec2 describe-instances`\n- `aws lambda list-functions` → `rtk aws lambda list-functions`\n- `aws logs get-log-events` → `rtk aws logs get-log-events`\n- `aws s3 ls` → `rtk aws s3 ls`\n- `aws cloudformation describe-stack-events` → `rtk aws cloudformation describe-stack-events`\n\n### Data & Utilities\n- `curl` → `rtk curl`\n- `wget` → `rtk wget`\n- `env` → `rtk env`\n- JSON files → `rtk json <file>`\n\n### Compound Commands (&&, ||, ;)\n- Rewrite BOTH sides: `cargo fmt && cargo test` → `rtk cargo fmt && rtk cargo test`\n- For pipes (|): Only rewrite LEFT side: `git log | head` → `rtk git log | head`\n\n## DO NOT REWRITE:\n- Commands already prefixed with `rtk`\n- `npm install` / `bun install` / `pnpm install` / `yarn install` (need full output)\n- `npm run dev` / `bun dev` / dev servers (long-running)\n- `npx` commands (package runners)\n- `cd` / `mkdir` / `rm` / `mv` / `cp` (filesystem mutations)\n- `echo` / `printf` / `export` / `set` (shell builtins)\n- `code` / `vim` / `nano` (editors)\n- Heredocs (<<)\n- Commands with complex redirects (> >> 2>&1)\n- `nuxt dev` / `nuxt build` / `nuxt generate` (framework commands needing full output)\n\n## ACTION:\nIf the command matches a rewrite rule above, execute the RTK version instead. If it doesn't match or is in the DO NOT REWRITE list, proceed with the original command unchanged."
  }
}
